# Admin Contracts Tab

When adding a contract that must appear in `http://localhost:3002/admin` -> `Contracts`:

1. Ensure `packages/config/index.ts` exposes `<feature>ContractAddress` and each env config sets it.
2. Add the contract to `apps/frontend/src/constants/contractList.ts` with the exact on-chain roles.
3. Add a `ContractDetailsCard` in `apps/frontend/src/app/admin/components/ContractsDetails.tsx` with the same config address.
4. Use the canonical contract name for the visible card title. Do not translate contract names in the admin contracts tab.
5. Verify the contract also appears in role-management UI via `CONTRACT_LIST`.

Example for Challenges:

- `config.challengesContractAddress`
- roles: `DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE`, `UPGRADER_ROLE`, `CONTRACTS_ADDRESS_MANAGER_ROLE`, `SETTINGS_MANAGER_ROLE`
